[[File:Nyratagira.jpg|thumb|250px|Nyrat Agira wearing Zoosha fabric.]]

'''Zoosha fabric''' was a soluble material available in [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]].<ref name="VD">''[[Star Wars: The Complete Visual Dictionary]]''</ref> The [[Human/Legends|Human]] clubgoer [[Nyrat Agira/Legends|Nyrat Agira]] wore fashionably impractical clothes made from zoosha fabric.<ref name="db">{{DB|character|nyratagira|Agira, Nyrat}}</ref>

In [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]],<ref name="NEC">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]'' dates the events of {{Film|II}} to [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]].</ref> Agira wore a pair of sheer, red-colored zoosha<ref name="VD" /> leggings<ref name="Depth">{{HomeVideoCite|film=2|featurette=Depth Commentary}}</ref> to the [[Outlander Club/Legends|Outlander Club]],<ref name="AotC" /> a [[Nightclub/Legends|nightclub]] and [[Gambling/Legends|gambling]] hall in the [[Uscru Entertainment District/Legends|Uscru Entertainment District]]<ref name="CSWE">{{CSWECite|II|431|Outlander Club}}</ref> of the [[Planet/Legends|planet]]<ref name="VD" /> [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]].<ref name="CSWE" /> In [[8 ABY/Legends|8 ABY]],<ref name="TERC">''[[The Essential Reader's Companion]]'' dates the events of ''[[Corphelion Interlude|Cophelion Interlude]]'' to [[8 ABY/Legends|8 ABY]].</ref> the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]] member<ref name="VD" /> [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa]] dressed comfortably but fashionably in a pair of slinky zoosha pants during her and her partner [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo's]] honeymoon to see the [[Corphelion Comets]] over<ref name="Interlude">{{StoryCite|story=Corphelion Interlude|book=A Forest Apart}}</ref> the [[Expansion Region/Legends|Expansion Region]]<ref name="EAOC">{{SW|url=news/star-wars-the-essential-atlas-online-companion|text=''Star Wars: The Essential Atlas'' Online Companion|int=Star Wars: The Essential Atlas Online Companion}}</ref> [[Asteroid/Legends|asteroid]] [[Corphelion]]. Solo found Organa's pants especially alluring.<ref name="Interlude" />

{{Clothes-stub}}
==Behind the scenes==
{{Quote|Either the Coruscant night air is usually toasty or zoosha fabric has amazing thermal properties. How else to explain Nyrat Agira's minimalist taste in clothing?|Daniel Wallace|<ref name="Who'sWho>{{InsiderCite|75|Who's Who in the Outlander Club: It's Ladies' Night}}</ref>}}
Zoosha fabric first appeared in the [[prequel trilogy]] film [[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones|''Star Wars'': Episode II ''Attack of the Clones'']].<ref name="AotC">{{Film|II}}</ref>

